{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UhCzjunxjfL4FG1SHJohdX","type":"tool_result","content":"# GitHub Issue Summary: Implement task-api Component\n\n## Core Details\n- **Issue Title:** Implement component: task-api #1\n- **Task ID:** b1529697-5681-41dc-afb8-6bd84e7ff401\n- **Component:** task-api (Go/net/http service)\n- **Port:** 9090\n- **Database:** SQLite at `/data/tasks.db`\n\n## Key Responsibilities\nThe task-api service must \"persist and manage all task data\" including title, due date, category, and completion state. It provides a RESTful interface with filtering capabilities and serves as the authoritative data source with no external dependencies.\n\n## Primary Endpoints Required\n- `GET /health` — status check\n- `GET /tasks` — list with optional category/completed filters\n- `POST /tasks` — create new task (server-side UUID generation)\n- `GET /tasks/{id}` — retrieve single task\n- `PUT /tasks/{id}` — update task\n- `DELETE /tasks/{id}` — remove task\n- `PATCH /tasks/{id}/complete` — toggle completion\n- `GET /categories` — distinct sorted category list\n\n## Critical Technical Requirements\n- **SQLite concurrency:** Use WAL mode or single connection pool to prevent \"database is locked\" errors\n- **CORS:** Handle OPTIONS preflight requests before route matching\n- **Date handling:** Store dueDate as nullable TEXT (YYYY-MM-DD); accept null and empty strings\n- **Build:** Multi-stage Dockerfile installing gcc and musl-dev for CGO support\n- **Error responses:** Return 4xx status with `{\"error\":\"message\"}` format\n\n## Validation Rules\nTitle must be non-empty and under 256 characters; UUIDs generated server-side only; timestamps in UTC ISO 8601 format."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fd88b737-f134-45c9-80b2-85007266868f","uuid":"97ee2166-bbdb-49d4-9346-323befe4bdda","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:55:24.912Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":382870,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# GitHub Issue Summary: Implement task-api Component\n\n## Core Details\n- **Issue Title:** Implement component: task-api #1\n- **Task ID:** b1529697-5681-41dc-afb8-6bd84e7ff401\n- **Component:** task-api (Go/net/http service)\n- **Port:** 9090\n- **Database:** SQLite at `/data/tasks.db`\n\n## Key Responsibilities\nThe task-api service must \"persist and manage all task data\" including title, due date, category, and completion state. It provides a RESTful interface with filtering capabilities and serves as the authoritative data source with no external dependencies.\n\n## Primary Endpoints Required\n- `GET /health` — status check\n- `GET /tasks` — list with optional category/completed filters\n- `POST /tasks` — create new task (server-side UUID generation)\n- `GET /tasks/{id}` — retrieve single task\n- `PUT /tasks/{id}` — update task\n- `DELETE /tasks/{id}` — remove task\n- `PATCH /tasks/{id}/complete` — toggle completion\n- `GET /categories` — distinct sorted category list\n\n## Critical Technical Requirements\n- **SQLite concurrency:** Use WAL mode or single connection pool to prevent \"database is locked\" errors\n- **CORS:** Handle OPTIONS preflight requests before route matching\n- **Date handling:** Store dueDate as nullable TEXT (YYYY-MM-DD); accept null and empty strings\n- **Build:** Multi-stage Dockerfile installing gcc and musl-dev for CGO support\n- **Error responses:** Return 4xx status with `{\"error\":\"message\"}` format\n\n## Validation Rules\nTitle must be non-empty and under 256 characters; UUIDs generated server-side only; timestamps in UTC ISO 8601 format.","durationMs":7960,"url":"https://github.com/asdlc-repos/kaj-test-14182/issues/1"}}
